entry.def: A blackout is a period of time during a war in which towns and buildings are made dark so that they cannot be seen by enemy planes.

entry.tran: （新闻等的）禁播，封锁，禁止出版
entry.def: If a blackout is imposed on a particular piece of news, journalists are prevented from broadcasting or publishing it.

example.ex: ...a media blackout imposed by the Imperial Palace...
Journalists said there was a virtual news blackout about the rally.

entry.def: If there is a power blackout, the electricity supply to a place is temporarily cut off.

example.ex: There was an electricity black-out in a large area in the north of the country.
example.tran: 该国北部大片地区断电。

entry.def: If you have a blackout, you temporarily lose consciousness.

example.ex: I suffered a black-out which lasted for several minutes.
